Package: flowr
Title: Static Dataflow Analysis and Program Slicing for R via flowR
Version: 0.2.9
Authors@R: c(
    person("Florian", "Sihler", email = "florian.sihler@uni-ulm.de", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("flowr-analysis", role = "cph"))
Description: Static dataflow analysis and program slicing for R, powered by
    flowR. Reduce a script to just the statements that affect a chosen variable
    ('slicing'), extract what it depends on (libraries, sourced files, data read
    and written), lint it against flowR's rules, run flowR's query API, and
    drive its read-eval-print loop --- helping you understand, debug, test and
    refactor unfamiliar or large R code
    without reading all of it. The analysis runs in a local flowR server that
    the package obtains through any of several interchangeable engines: flowR's
    JavaScript and WebAssembly bundle shipped with the package (run on
    'Node.js'), a self-contained downloaded binary, a system or private
    'Node.js' install, or 'Docker'.
License: GPL-3
